Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getIlmMode(25.10)                                            getIlmMode(25.10)

Name
       getIlmMode  - Displays information about the specified setIlmMode para-
       meter in the Innovus log file and in the Innovus console

Syntax
       getIlmMode

       [-filterInternalPath]

       [-ilm]

       [-ilm <ilmName>]

       [-keepAsync {true|false}]

       [-keepFlatten {true|false}]

       [-keepHighFanoutPorts {true|false}]

       [-keepInstInSdc {true|false}]

       [-keepLoopBack {true|false}]

       [-map {view|corner}]

       [-maxNumInsts]

       [-maxNumRegisters]

       [-resetMap {view|corner}]

       [-slackDriven]

       [-top <topViewName>]

       [-quiet]

       Displays information about the specified setIlmMode  parameter  in  the
       Innovus log file and in the Innovus console. Displays the following in-
       formation.

              * Parameter name

              * Current value

              * Type (Boolean, string, and so on)

              * Whether the current value was set by user

       If  you  do  not specify a parameter, the software displays information
       for all of the setIlmMode parameters.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each getIlmMode parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man getIlmMode

       <parameter_names>
              Displays information for the specified parameters. You can spec-
              ify one or more parameters.

       -quiet Displays  the  current  settings for the specified parameters in
              Tcl list format only.

              If you specify -quiet without any parameters, the software  dis-
              plays  the  current settings of all setILMMode parameters in Tcl
              format.

Examples
              * The following example displays the  current  setting  for  the
                -keepAsync parameter:

                getIlmMode -keepAsync

                The software displays the following information:

                -keepAsync false # bool, default=false

                false

              * The  following  command  displays the current settings for all
                setIlmMode parameters:

                getIlmMode

                The software displays the following information:

                -keepAsync false # bool, default=false

                -keepHighFanoutPorts true # bool, default=true

                -keepLoopBack false # bool, default=false

                {keepAsync  false}  {keepHighFanoutPorts  true}  {keepLoopBack
                false}

              * The  following  command  displays  the current setting for the
                -keepHighFanoutPorts parameter in Tcl list format only:

                getIlmMode -keepHighFanoutPorts -quiet

                The software displays the following information:

                true

              * The following command reports which view  of  ILM,  blkA,  has
                been mapped to the top analysis view of maxDelay:

                getIlmMode -map view -top maxDelay -ilmCell blkA

              * The  following command reports all the corner mappings of ILM,
                blkA, that have been mapped to the top analysis corners:

                getIlmMode -map corner ilmCell blkA

              * The following command reports all the view  mappings  for  all
                ILMs:

                getIlmMode -map view

              * The  following  command  displays the current settings for all
                setIlmMode parameters in Tcl list format only:

                getIlmMode -quiet

                The software displays the following information:

                {keepAsync  false}  {keepHighFanoutPorts  true}  {keepLoopBack
                false}

Related Information
